notes: Australia 76 runs from the 1st 20 overs, 157 from the 2nd 20 overs.
SR Waugh 5th Australian to score 4000 runs in ODIs.
SR Waugh and ME Waugh partnership: 50 runs from 76 balls 100 runs from 113 balls (50 off 37) 150 runs from 164 balls (50 off 51) 200 runs from 198 balls (50 off 34)

SR Waugh and ME Waugh 207 for the 3rd wicket, 7th highest ever ODI partnership for any wicket, 3rd highest ODI 3rd wicket partnership, 1st ever 200 run two-man partnership in the World Cup (Haynes, Lara and Richardson combined for 221 runs v PAK in 1992), 2nd highest 3rd wicket partnership for Australia, 3rd highest for Australia for any wicket.
ME Waugh 130 off 128 balls, 14x4 1x6, equal 3rd highest ODI individual score for Australia, highest ever for Australia in the World Cup.
5th highest ODI team score for Australia (highest for Australia since May 1990).
CJ McDermott left the field injured at the end of the 5th over, Slater substituted.
KO Otieno and MO Odumbe 102, first ever 100 run partnership for Kenya in ODIs.
KO Otieno dropped by S Waugh on 77.
KO Otieno retired hurt on 82* from 166/3 to 188/5 (leg cramp)

milestones.description: Otieno has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (38) in an innings in ODIs for KENYA, going past Steve Tikolo's 22
Martin Suji has broken the record for most catches (3) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Rajab Ali's 1
Otieno and Odumbe's 102-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 96 between Steve Tikolo and Odumbe
Tito Odumbe and David Tikolo's 21-run partnership is KENYA's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 4 between Hitesh Modi and Thomas Odoyo
Otieno has become the top scorer for KENYA in ODIs with 112 runs, going past Steve Tikolo's 65
Thomas Odoyo has conceded the most runs in an innings (58) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Odumbe's record of 39
Rajab Ali has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (2) for KENYA, going past Chudasama
Rajab Ali has become the top wicket-taker for KENYA in ODIs with 3 wickets, going past Steve Tikolo's 1
Otieno's 85 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for KENYA), surpassing Steve Tikolo's 65
Martin Suji has broken the record for most catches in an innings (2) in ODIs for KENYA, going past Rajab Ali's 1
Otieno and Odumbe's 102-run partnership is KENYA's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 96 between Odumbe and Steve Tikolo
